views.name: All letters that are not followed up

rows.field_34708:
Hello Santa,\
Are you excited about delivering gifts? I can’t wait! Could you bring me a set of crayons and a coloring book? I want to make drawings to send back to you next year.

Love,\
Evelyn
rows.field_34711:
Ho, ho, ho! What a wonderful letter, my dear boy! I’m so happy to hear that you’re excited for Christmas—it’s my favorite time of year too. Crayons and a coloring book sound like the perfect way to spread your creativity and Christmas cheer.

The elves have already started packing your special gift, and I’ll make sure it’s on my sleigh for Christmas Eve. I can’t wait to see the wonderful drawings you’ll create! Don’t forget to leave some cookies and milk for me—and maybe a carrot or two for the reindeer.

Stay kind and keep being creative, James!

Merry Christmas,\
**Santa Claus** 🎅

rows.field_34708:
Dear Santa Claus,

I hope Rudolph’s nose is shining bright! For Christmas, I’d love a cozy new blanket and maybe a book about dinosaurs. I’ll leave cookies and milk for you (and carrots for the reindeer).

Hugs,

Mia

Hi Santa,

\
Hi! I’m super excited about Christmas. I hope you’re staying warm at the North Pole. This year, I’d love a big box of building blocks to make cool castles. Say hi to the elves for me!

Merry Christmas,\
Amelia

Dear Santa,

\
I’ve been trying really hard to be good this year! I hope you and the reindeer are ready for Christmas Eve. Could you please bring me a new soccer ball? I promise to share it with my friends!

Thank you so much,\
Evelyn

Dear Santa,

My name is Isabella, and I’m 6 years old. I have been super good this year. I help my mommy with my baby brother, and I always clean my room. For Christmas, I would love a dollhouse with little furniture and people. I promise to take care of it and share it with my friends when they visit. Thank you, Santa!

Love,

Isabella

Hi Santa,

It’s me, Noah! I’m 10, and I hope you and the reindeer are doing okay. This year I tried to do better in school and help Dad with yard work. For Christmas, I’d really like a soccer ball, so I can practice and get better at my favorite sport. My little sister wants a teddy bear too! Thanks, Santa, and say hi to Mrs. Claus for me!

Your friend,\
Noah ⚽

Dear Santa Claus,

I hope you’re having fun in the North Pole. My name is Mia, and I’m 8 years old. I’ve been working hard on being nicer to my little brother, even when he takes my toys. For Christmas, I would love some books to read because I love adventures and learning new things. Maybe you could also bring something small for my cat, Luna? She’s been a good kitty too!

Merry Christmas,\
Mia 📚

Dear Santa,

It’s your pal, Evelyn. Can you believe that I’m 3 ½ now? Thanks for all the great gifts last year. I baked a lot of cookies! I’ve been the best girl that I can be this year. I would like to ask you to bring me a doctor’s trolley and a Dora couch. A few surprises would be nice too. Please be good to kids everywhere. I’ll leave milk and cookies for you and the Santa key.

I love you!

Evelyn ❤️

Ho ho ho from the North Pole! I've found the perfect gift for you and I'll be visiting you soon! Stay joyful and merry!

Santa Claus!

fields.name: Estimated workload for today
fields.formula: sum(filter(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Estimated completion time'),lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Scheduled') = today()))

fields.name: Open estimated workload for today
fields.formula: sum(filter(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Estimated completion time'),and(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Scheduled') = today(),totext(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Status')) != 'Completed')))

fields.name: Completed actual workload for today
fields.formula: sum(filter(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Actual completion time'),and(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Scheduled') = today(),totext(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Status')) = 'Completed')))

fields.name: Open estimated workload for tomorrow
fields.formula: sum(filter(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Estimated completion time'),and(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Scheduled') = today() + date_interval('1 day'),totext(lookup('🪄💫Wish Fulfilments','Status')) != 'Completed')))
